% Testing Standards and Conventions
% Test Guidelines for InvoiceIQ

Python Tests:
1. Use pytest for all Python unit tests
2. Use pytest-asyncio for async test support
3. Use unittest.mock for mocking external services
4. Aim for 80%+ code coverage
5. Test file location: tests/test_<module_name>.py
6. Test naming: test_<function_name>_<scenario>
7. Use fixtures for reusable test data
8. Test both success and error paths

React Tests:
1. Use Vitest or Jest for component tests
2. Use React Testing Library for component testing
3. Test user interactions, not implementation details
4. Mock API calls with msw (Mock Service Worker)
5. Test file location: __tests__/<component_name>.test.jsx
6. Test naming: should_<action>_<expected_result>
7. Use data-testid for selecting elements in tests

Integration Tests:
1. Test full workflows (upload → extract → review → export)
2. Use docker-compose for database setup
3. Test error scenarios and edge cases
